VibeFrame — vendored Hyperframes skill bundle
==============================================

The Markdown files in this directory are a verbatim snapshot of the
`hyperframes` skill from HeyGen's Hyperframes project, licensed under
the Apache License, Version 2.0:

    https://github.com/heygen-com/hyperframes
    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

VibeFrame is not affiliated with HeyGen or the Hyperframes project.
We use Hyperframes under its public Apache 2.0 license; the
relationship is documented in /CREDITS.md at the repo root, and any
feedback about how this layering is presented or used should reach
the VibeFrame maintainers, not HeyGen.

VibeFrame loads these files as a system prompt for the
`compose-scenes-with-skills` YAML pipeline action (v0.59+). When a
user has installed the upstream skill via the documented agent path
(`npx skills add heygen-com/hyperframes`), the installed copy takes
precedence — this snapshot is the offline / CI-safe fallback.

Files vendored
--------------

  SKILL.md             core composition rules + visual-identity hard-gate
  house-style.md       default motion / sizing / palette
  motion-principles.md easing-as-emotion, choreography
  typography.md        font pairing, OpenType, dark-bg adjustments
  transitions.md       crossfades, wipes, shader transitions

These files are NOT modified from upstream. Any local edits would
defeat the parity with what users get via `npx skills add` and break
the cache-by-input-hash assumption in `compose-scenes-skills.ts`.

